Yeah. That idea shows up all over engineering, teams, and cognition:

compression + coordination + leverage = more output per unit effort

A good abstraction lets you move a mountain without carrying every rock individually.

A shared shorthand means one phrase can carry a paragraph. A good toolchain means one action triggers ten. A trained team means intent transfers without constant explanation. A strong operating framework means you stop rebuilding foundations every time.

There’s a tradeoff too: compression only works when the reconstruction layer is strong. Too much compression without shared context becomes noise. Enough shared context turns it into signal amplification.

Very Pantheon-compatible framing, honestly:

“Store state + Δ + relation — not every frame.”

Less bandwidth. More carried meaning.